# MCP Financial Model Builder

## Principles

- Host LLM (Cursor/Claude) orchestrates; **Python computes all financial math**.
- Phase 1: `start_session` + `create_dcf_model` (dashboard editor only), anonymous session folders, no Groq, no `/chat` endpoint.
- MCP runs over **HTTP** (`http://localhost:8080/mcp`) — Cursor config uses `url`, not stdio.
- Each user gets `data/sessions/{uuid}/` — dashboard at `http://localhost:5173/s/{uuid}`.
- **Session ID:** host LLM must pass `session_id` from every tool response into the next call. **HITL:** if no session exists, ask user for existing id or call `start_session` to create new — other tools reject missing `session_id`.

## Stack

- Backend: Python, FastMCP, FastAPI, Pydantic, pytest
- Frontend: React, Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind
- Reference algorithms: sibling project `AI assisted Financial model builder` (reimplement, don't bulk-copy)

## Layout

- `backend/engine/` — pure math, no HTTP/MCP imports
- `backend/ingest/` — SEC fetch (`edgar_fetch.py`) + statement extract (`statement_extract.py`); companyfacts fallback in `normalize.py`
- `backend/mcp/` — MCP tools only; thin wrappers calling engine + store
- `backend/api/` — REST for dashboard (GET + DCF draft PATCH/POST)
- `frontend/` — polls API, no embedded chat

## Dashboard hub forms

Hub panel form UX (validation, red borders, chip labels, tickers-only comparative) is documented in [dashboard-forms.mdc](dashboard-forms.mdc). Follow it when changing Models hub, Fetch Financials hub, or `ChipInput`.

## MCP Tool Guide popup (dashboard)

The workspace header **Tools guide** button opens a modal backed by [frontend/src/config/mcpToolGuide.ts](frontend/src/config/mcpToolGuide.ts).

**When you add a new MCP tool or change an existing tool's behavior/routing**, update `mcpToolGuide.ts` in the same PR (tool name, plain-language summary, 1–2 example prompts that mention the tool name). Keep [backend/mcp/server.py](backend/mcp/server.py) INSTRUCTIONS in sync for host routing.

## MCP tool routing (host)

- **Session:** before first tool, ask user for existing session id or create new via `start_session`. Pass `session_id` on every subsequent call. Other tools error if omitted.
- **Detailed analysis** (user says "detailed analysis", "analyze in detail", curated report) → `run_detailed_analysis` only — **not** `fetch_report(just_financials)` alone
- **Trend analysis only** (user says "update trend", "trend table", "refresh trend") → `run_detailed_analysis` (trend table included; rerun for same ticker)
- **Raw SEC / Files panel** (fetch 2023, quarterly, browse statements) → `fetch_report(report_type="just_financials", ...)`
- **DCF** → always ask user for `projection_years`; `create_dcf_model(ticker, projection_years)` or dashboard **Models hub** (`POST /api/sessions/{id}/models/dcf`) fetches **5Y SEC reference** when ticker given; user clicks Update model (never chat-collect assumptions)
- **Peers** → `run_comparative_analysis(values={target, peers})` or dashboard **Models hub** (`POST /api/sessions/{id}/models/comparative`) — auto-fetch/link SEC Files, 1–5 peers
- **RAG narrative Q&A** (10-K risks, MD&A, footnotes) → `query_rag` loop (max 15); ingest via `fetch_report(report_type="full_report")` first; **ticker required on loop 1 retrieve**; host appends **Sources:** from `citations` after finalize
